{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":920,"text":"So there's this thing called\nthe law of unintended consequences."},{"time":5400,"text":"I thought it was just like a saying,"},{"time":7160,"text":"but it actually exists, I guess."},{"time":8760,"text":"There's, like, academic papers about it."},{"time":11120,"text":"And I'm a designer."},{"time":12400,"text":"I don't like unintended consequences."},{"time":15280,"text":"People hire me because they have\nconsequences that they really intend,"},{"time":19880,"text":"and what they intend is for me\nto help them achieve those consequences."},{"time":23760,"text":"So I live in fear\nof unintended consequences."},{"time":26800,"text":"And so this is a story about\nconsequences intended and unintended."}]},{"cues":[{"time":32080,"text":"I got called by an organization\ncalled Robin Hood"},{"time":35240,"text":"to do a favor for them."},{"time":36840,"text":"Robin Hood is based in New York,\na wonderful philanthropic organization"},{"time":40280,"text":"that does what it says in the name."},{"time":42040,"text":"They take from rich people,\ngive it to poor people."},{"time":44840,"text":"In this case, what they wanted to benefit\nwas the New York City school system,"},{"time":49760,"text":"a huge enterprise that educates\nmore than a million students at a time,"},{"time":55120,"text":"and in buildings that are like this one,"},{"time":57480,"text":"old buildings, big buildings,"},{"time":59400,"text":"drafty buildings, sometimes buildings\nthat are in disrepair,"},{"time":62560,"text":"certainly buildings\nthat could use a renovation."},{"time":65120,"text":"Robin Hood had this ambition\nto improve these buildings in some way,"},{"time":68400,"text":"but what they realized was"},{"time":69880,"text":"to fix the buildings would be\ntoo expensive and impractical."},{"time":74440,"text":"So instead they tried to figure out\nwhat one room they could go into"},{"time":78840,"text":"in each of these buildings,\nin as many buildings that they could,"},{"time":81920,"text":"and fix that one room"},{"time":84600,"text":"so that they could improve\nthe lives of the children inside"},{"time":87440,"text":"as they were studying."},{"time":88680,"text":"And what they came up with\nwas the school library,"},{"time":91120,"text":"and they came up with this idea\ncalled the Library Initiative."},{"time":94080,"text":"All the students\nhave to pass through the library."},{"time":96480,"text":"That's where the books are."},{"time":97840,"text":"That's where the heart\nand soul of the school is."},{"time":100200,"text":"So let's fix these libraries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":101640,"text":"So they did this wonderful thing\nwhere they brought in"},{"time":104200,"text":"first 10, then 20, then more architects,"},{"time":107320,"text":"each one of whom was assigned a library\nto rethink what a library was."},{"time":111080,"text":"They trained special librarians."},{"time":113160,"text":"So they started this mighty enterprise"},{"time":115240,"text":"to reform public schools\nby improving these libraries."},{"time":118280,"text":"Then they called me up and they said,\n\"Could you make a little contribution?\""},{"time":121960,"text":"I said, \"Sure, what do you want me to do?\""},{"time":124000,"text":"And they said, \"Well, we want you\nto be the graphic designer"},{"time":126880,"text":"in charge of the whole thing.\""},{"time":128360,"text":"And so I thought, I know what that means.\nThat means I get to design a logo."},{"time":131960,"text":"I know how to design that. I design logos."},{"time":134000,"text":"That's what people come to me for."},{"time":135680,"text":"So OK, let's design a logo for this thing."},{"time":137800,"text":"Easy to do, actually,\ncompared with architecture"},{"time":140080,"text":"and being a librarian."},{"time":141360,"text":"Just do a logo, make a contribution,\nand then you're out,"},{"time":144120,"text":"and you feel really good about yourself."},{"time":146080,"text":"And I'm a great guy and I like to feel\ngood about myself when I do these favors."}]},{"cues":[{"time":149880,"text":"So I thought, let's overdeliver."},{"time":151480,"text":"I'm going to give you three logos,\nall based on this one idea."},{"time":154440,"text":"So you have three options,\npick any of the three."},{"time":156800,"text":"They're all great, I said."},{"time":158120,"text":"So the basic idea was\nthese would be new school libraries"},{"time":161360,"text":"for New York schools,"},{"time":162920,"text":"and so the idea is that it's a new thing,\na new idea that needs a new name."},{"time":166800,"text":"What I wanted to do was dispel the idea\nthat these were musty old libraries,"},{"time":171840,"text":"the kind of places\nthat everyone is bored with,"},{"time":175480,"text":"you know, not your grandparents' library."},{"time":177480,"text":"Don't worry about that at all."},{"time":178960,"text":"This is going to this new, exciting thing,"},{"time":181000,"text":"not a boring library."}]},{"cues":[{"time":182280,"text":"So option number one:"},{"time":183960,"text":"so instead of thinking of it as a library,"},{"time":186000,"text":"think of it as a place where it is like:\ndo talk, do make loud noises."},{"time":190200,"text":"Right? So no shushing,\nit's like a shush-free zone."},{"time":194240,"text":"We're going to call it the Reading Room."}]},{"cues":[{"time":196440,"text":"That was option number one.\nOK, option number two."},{"time":199840,"text":"Option number two was, wait for it,"},{"time":203280,"text":"OWL."},{"time":204560,"text":"I'll meet you at OWL."},{"time":205920,"text":"I'm getting my book from the OWL.\nMeet you after school down at OWL."},{"time":209240,"text":"I like that, right?\nNow, what does OWL stand for?"},{"time":211600,"text":"Well, it could be One World Library,"},{"time":213520,"text":"or it could be Open. Wonder. Learn."},{"time":216160,"text":"Or it could be -- and I figure librarians\ncould figure out other things it could be"},{"time":220680,"text":"because they know about words."},{"time":222160,"text":"So other things, right?"},{"time":223400,"text":"And then look at this.\nIt's like the eye of the owl."},{"time":225880,"text":"This is irresistible in my opinion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":227600,"text":"But there's even another idea."},{"time":229080,"text":"Option number three."},{"time":230320,"text":"Option number three\nwas based actually on language."},{"time":232960,"text":"It's the idea that \"read\"\nis the past tense of \"read,\""},{"time":236280,"text":"and they're both spelled the same way."},{"time":238160,"text":"So why don't we call\nthis place The Red Zone?"},{"time":241120,"text":"I'll meet you at the Red Zone."},{"time":242573,"text":"Are you Red? Get Red."},{"time":245880,"text":"I'm well Red."}]},{"cues":[{"time":247120,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":248360,"text":"I really loved this idea,"},{"time":249720,"text":"and I somehow was not focused on the idea"},{"time":252080,"text":"that librarians as a class are sort of\ninterested in spelling and I don't know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":258000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":259959,"text":"But sometimes cleverness\nis more important than spelling,"},{"time":263480,"text":"and I thought this would be\none of those instances."},{"time":265920,"text":"So usually when I make these presentations"},{"time":267960,"text":"I say there's just one question\nand the question should be,"},{"time":270760,"text":"\"How can I thank you, Mike?\""},{"time":272160,"text":"But in this case,\nthe question was more like,"},{"time":274800,"text":"\"Um, are you kidding?\""},{"time":277240,"text":"Because, they said,"},{"time":278960,"text":"the premise of all this work"},{"time":280360,"text":"was that kids were bored\nwith old libraries, musty old libraries."},{"time":284520,"text":"They were tired of them."},{"time":285760,"text":"And instead, they said, these kids\nhave never really seen a library."},{"time":289120,"text":"The school libraries in these schools"},{"time":290960,"text":"are really so dilapidated,\nif they're there at all,"},{"time":294400,"text":"that they haven't bored anyone."},{"time":296360,"text":"They haven't even been there\nto bore anyone at all."},{"time":299360,"text":"So the idea was, just forget\nabout giving it a new name."},{"time":302800,"text":"Just call it, one last try, a library."},{"time":306880,"text":"Right? OK."},{"time":308120,"text":"So I thought, OK, give it a little oomph?"},{"time":311000,"text":"Exclamation point?"},{"time":312240,"text":"Then -- this is because I'm clever --"},{"time":314240,"text":"move that into the \"i,\""},{"time":316800,"text":"make it red,"},{"time":318080,"text":"and there you have it,\nthe Library Initiative."},{"time":320280,"text":"So I thought, mission accomplished,\nthere's your logo."},{"time":322840,"text":"So what's interesting about this logo,\nan unintended consequence,"},{"time":325920,"text":"was that it turned out that\nthey didn't really even need my design"},{"time":329080,"text":"because you could type it any font,\nyou could write it by hand,"},{"time":332080,"text":"and when they started\nsending emails around,"},{"time":334200,"text":"they just would use Shift and 1,"},{"time":335800,"text":"they'd get their own logo\njust right out of the thing."},{"time":338400,"text":"And I thought, well, that's fine."},{"time":340160,"text":"Feel free to use that logo."},{"time":341960,"text":"And then I embarked\non the real rollout of this thing --"},{"time":344880,"text":"working with every one of the architects"},{"time":346840,"text":"to put this logo on the front door\nof their own library. Right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":350360,"text":"So here's the big rollout."},{"time":351760,"text":"Basically I'd work\nwith different architects."},{"time":354040,"text":"First Robin Hood was my client.\nNow these architects were my client."},{"time":357280,"text":"I'd say, \"Here's your logo.\nPut it on the door.\""},{"time":359543,"text":"\"Here's your logo. Put it on both doors.\""},{"time":361520,"text":"\"Here's your logo.\nPut it off to the side.\""},{"time":363560,"text":"\"Here's your logo\nrepeated all over to the top.\""},{"time":365840,"text":"So everything was going swimmingly."},{"time":367560,"text":"I just was saying,\n\"Here's your logo. Here's your logo.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":370240,"text":"Then I got a call\nfrom one of the architects,"},{"time":372400,"text":"a guy named Richard Lewis,\nand he says, \"I've got a problem."},{"time":375280,"text":"You're the graphics guy.\nCan you solve it?\""},{"time":377320,"text":"And I said, OK, sure.\""},{"time":378560,"text":"And he said, \"The problem is\nthat there's a space"},{"time":381160,"text":"between the shelf and the ceiling.\""},{"time":383000,"text":"So that sounds like\nan architectural issue to me,"},{"time":385360,"text":"not a graphic design issue,\nso I'm, \"Go on.\""},{"time":387480,"text":"And Richard says, \"Well,\nthe top shelf has to be low enough"},{"time":391160,"text":"for the kid to reach it,"},{"time":392400,"text":"but I'm in a big old building,\nand the ceilings are really high,"},{"time":395424,"text":"so actually I've got\nall this space up there"},{"time":397520,"text":"and I need something like a mural.\""},{"time":399240,"text":"And I'm like, \"Whoa,\nyou know, I'm a logo designer."},{"time":402200,"text":"I'm not Diego Rivera or something."},{"time":404360,"text":"I'm not a muralist.\""},{"time":406000,"text":"And so he said, \"But can't you\nthink of anything?\""},{"time":408400,"text":"So I said, \"OK, what if we just\ntook pictures of the kids in the school"},{"time":413800,"text":"and just put them around\nthe top of the thing,"},{"time":416280,"text":"and maybe that could work.\""},{"time":417640,"text":"And my wife is a photographer,"},{"time":419520,"text":"and I said, \"Dorothy, there's no budget,"},{"time":421480,"text":"can you come to this school\nin east New York, take these pictures?\""},{"time":424680,"text":"And she did,"},{"time":425920,"text":"and if you go in Richard's library,"},{"time":427920,"text":"which is one of the first that opened,"},{"time":429800,"text":"it has this glorious frieze\nof, like, the heroes of the school,"},{"time":432920,"text":"oversized, looking down"},{"time":434640,"text":"into the little dollhouse\nof the real library, right?"},{"time":437680,"text":"And the kids were great,\nhand-selected by the principals"},{"time":440520,"text":"and the librarian."},{"time":442320,"text":"It just kind of created\nthis heroic atmosphere in this library,"},{"time":445600,"text":"this very dignified setting below\nand the joy of the children above."}]},{"cues":[{"time":449120,"text":"So naturally all the other librarians\nin the other schools see this"},{"time":453480,"text":"and they said, well, we want murals too."},{"time":455440,"text":"And I'm like, OK."},{"time":456760,"text":"So then I think, well,\nit can't be the same mural every time,"},{"time":459680,"text":"so Dorothy did another one,\nand then she did another one,"},{"time":462760,"text":"but then we needed more help,"},{"time":464400,"text":"so I called an illustrator I knew\nnamed Lynn Pauley,"},{"time":467280,"text":"and Lynn did these beautiful\npaintings of the kids."},{"time":470240,"text":"Then I called a guy named Charles Wilkin\nat a place called Automatic Design."},{"time":474600,"text":"He did these amazing collages."},{"time":476960,"text":"We had Rafael Esquer"},{"time":479320,"text":"do these great silhouettes."},{"time":481200,"text":"He would work with the kids,\nasking for words,"},{"time":483400,"text":"and then based on those prompts,"},{"time":485000,"text":"come up with this little,\ndelirious kind of constellation"},{"time":487720,"text":"of silhouettes\nof things that are in books."},{"time":489800,"text":"Peter Arkle interviewed the kids"},{"time":491400,"text":"and had them talk\nabout their favorite books"},{"time":493520,"text":"and he put their testimony\nas a frieze up there."},{"time":495800,"text":"Stefan Sagmeister worked with Yuko Shimizu"},{"time":498080,"text":"and they did this amazing\nmanga-style statement,"},{"time":500400,"text":"\"Everyone who is honest is interesting,\""},{"time":502880,"text":"that goes all the way around."},{"time":504760,"text":"Christoph Niemann, brilliant illustrator,"},{"time":507160,"text":"did a whole series of things"},{"time":508560,"text":"where he embedded books\ninto the faces and characters"},{"time":511600,"text":"and images and places\nthat you find in the books."},{"time":514760,"text":"And then even Maira Kalman"},{"time":516840,"text":"did this amazing cryptic installation\nof objects and words"},{"time":520679,"text":"that kind of go all around\nand will fascinate students"},{"time":523880,"text":"for as long as it's up there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":525480,"text":"So this was really satisfying,"},{"time":527160,"text":"and basically my role here was reading\na series of dimensions to these artists,"},{"time":533080,"text":"and I would say,"},{"time":534360,"text":"\"Three feet by 15 feet, whatever you want."},{"time":537080,"text":"Let me know if you have\nany problem with that.\""},{"time":539320,"text":"And they would go and install these.\nIt just was the greatest thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":542560,"text":"But the greatest thing, actually, was --"},{"time":544880,"text":"Every once in a while,"},{"time":546120,"text":"I'd get, like, an invitation in the mail\nmade of construction paper,"},{"time":549360,"text":"and it would say, \"You are invited\nto the opening of our new library.\""},{"time":552680,"text":"So you'd go to the library,\nsay, you'd go to PS10,"},{"time":555080,"text":"and you'd go inside."},{"time":556320,"text":"There'd be balloons,\nthere'd be a student ambassador,"},{"time":559120,"text":"there'd be speeches that were read,"},{"time":561280,"text":"poetry that was written\nspecifically for the opening,"},{"time":564200,"text":"dignitaries would present people\nwith certificates,"},{"time":567160,"text":"and the whole thing\nwas just a delirious, fun party."},{"time":569800,"text":"So I loved going to these things."},{"time":571440,"text":"I would stand there dressed like this,\nobviously not belonging,"},{"time":574440,"text":"and someone would say,\n\"What are you doing here, mister?\""},{"time":577131,"text":"And I'd say, \"Well, I'm part of the team\nthat designed this place.\""},{"time":580320,"text":"And they'd said, \"You do these shelves?\""},{"time":582249,"text":"And I said, \"No.\"\n\"You took the pictures up above.\""},{"time":584680,"text":"\"No.\""},{"time":585920,"text":"\"Well, what did you do?\""},{"time":587160,"text":"\"You know when you came in?\nThe sign over the door?\""},{"time":589640,"text":"\"The sign that says library?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":591080,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":592120,"text":"\"Yeah, I did that!\""},{"time":593360,"text":"And then they'd sort of go,\n\"OK. Nice work if you can get it.\""},{"time":598200,"text":"So it was so satisfying\ngoing to these little openings"},{"time":602320,"text":"despite the fact that I was\nkind of largely ignored or humiliated,"},{"time":606080,"text":"but it was actually fun\ngoing to the openings,"},{"time":608280,"text":"so I decided that I wanted\nto get the people in my office"},{"time":611000,"text":"who had worked on these projects,\nget the illustrators and photographers,"},{"time":614480,"text":"and I said, why don't we rent a van"},{"time":616200,"text":"and drive around\nthe five boroughs of New York"},{"time":618600,"text":"and see how many we could hit at one time."},{"time":620640,"text":"And eventually there were\ngoing to be 60 of these libraries,"},{"time":623520,"text":"so we probably got to see\nmaybe half a dozen in one long day."},{"time":627320,"text":"And the best thing of all\nwas meeting these librarians"},{"time":630280,"text":"who kind of were running these,\ntook possession of these places"},{"time":633880,"text":"like their private stage\nupon which they were invited"},{"time":636480,"text":"to mesmerize their students\nand bring the books to life,"},{"time":640440,"text":"and it was just\nthis really exciting experience"},{"time":643000,"text":"for all of us to actually\nsee these things in action."},{"time":645840,"text":"So we spent a long day doing this"},{"time":648400,"text":"and we were in the very last library."},{"time":650240,"text":"It was still winter,\nbecause it got dark early,"},{"time":653080,"text":"and the librarian says,"},{"time":654320,"text":"\"I'm about to close down.\nSo really nice having you here."},{"time":657040,"text":"Hey, wait a second, do you want to see\nhow I turn off the lights?\""},{"time":660200,"text":"I'm like, \"OK.\""},{"time":661520,"text":"And she said, \"I have\nthis special way that I do it.\""},{"time":664040,"text":"And then she showed me."},{"time":665320,"text":"What she did was she turned out\nevery light one by one by one by one,"},{"time":668800,"text":"and the last light she left on"},{"time":670880,"text":"was the light that illuminated\nthe kids' faces,"},{"time":673800,"text":"and she said, \"That's the last light\nI turn off every night,"},{"time":676680,"text":"because I like to remind myself\nwhy I come to work.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":679280,"text":"So when I started this whole thing,"},{"time":682160,"text":"remember, it was just\nabout designing that logo"},{"time":684375,"text":"and being clever, come up with a new name?"},{"time":686400,"text":"The unintended consequence here,"},{"time":688000,"text":"which I would like to take credit for"},{"time":689840,"text":"and like to think I can think through\nthe experience to that extent,"},{"time":693080,"text":"but I can't."},{"time":694320,"text":"I was just focused on a foot ahead of me,\nas far as I could reach with my own hands."},{"time":698320,"text":"Instead, way off in the distance"},{"time":700920,"text":"was a librarian"},{"time":702200,"text":"who was going to find\nthe chain of consequences"},{"time":705160,"text":"that we had set in motion,"},{"time":706600,"text":"a source of inspiration"},{"time":708120,"text":"so that she in this case\ncould do her work really well."},{"time":711520,"text":"40,000 kids a year\nare affected by these libraries."},{"time":714920,"text":"They've been happening\nfor more than 10 years now,"},{"time":717400,"text":"so those librarians have kind of turned on\na generation of children to books"},{"time":721960,"text":"and so it's been a thrill to find out"},{"time":724480,"text":"that sometimes unintended consequences\nare the best consequences."}]},{"cues":[{"time":728240,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":729480,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}